Get remote table metadata

Source: R/get_metadata.R
get_metadata.Rd

Get remote table metadata

get_metadata(x)

Arguments

x

An object of class tbl_lazy produced by get_table()

Value

A named list of remote table metadata

Author

Ernest Guevarra

Examples

x <- get_table(con = connect_oxcovid19(), tbl_name = "epidemiology")
get_metadata(x)

#> $Name
#> <IDENT> epidemiology
#> 
#> $Source
#> src:  postgres  [covid19@covid19db.org:5432/covid19]
#> tbls: administrative_division, baseline_mortality, diagnostics, epidemiology,

#>   government_response, mobility, spatial_ref_sys, surveys, weather, world_bank,
#>   world_bank_time_series

#> FROM "epidemiology"
